FeedPackage.Description:
DW.CodedUI - Test your UI fast and easy.
Changes see changelog.
* Its written in .Net 4.0 * Its built to be used every visual studio version no matter if the MS "automated UI" is included or not * Its developed under the MIT license
This beta is the preview of a version which is planned to work at least in VS 2015 community edition (Kind of stand alone). Like for all my assemblies, even minor versions are releases, odds are betas like this one.
Stand-alone download: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Assembly.zip Changelog: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Changelog.txt Documentation: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Documentation
Scenario Example: * Visual Studio 2013 Premium is installed (Can be the unlicensed demo! It will never started.) * Visual Studio 2015 Community Edition should run UI tests. 1. Create a normal unit test project 2. Add reference the DW.CodedUI.dll 3. Add reference to "C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 12.0\Common7\IDE\PrivateAssemblies\Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UITest.Logging.dll" 4. Add reference to "C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 12.0\Common7\IDE\PublicAssemblies\UIAComWrapper.dll" 5. Add "C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 12.0\Common7\IDE\PublicAssemblies\Interop.UIAutomationClient.dll" as existing item (reference will not copy the file to the output directory) and set build action to "None" and "Copy Always"
Now with Visual Studio 2015 Community Edition UI tests can be executed in usual [TestClass] objects.
FeedPackage.Title: DW.CodedUI.Beta

FeedPackage.Description:
DW.CodedUI - Test your UI fast and easy.
Changes see changelog.
* Will run in all Visual Studio version up from 2010 * Its written in .Net 4.0 * Its developed under the MIT license
This beta is the preview of a version which is planned to work stand-alone in all visual studio versions. Like for all my assemblies, even minor versions are releases, odds are betas like this one.
Stand-alone download: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Assembly.zip Changelog: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Changelog.txt Documentation: http://libs.my-libraries.com/DW.CodedUI/v2.5.0/Documentation
Installation: 1. Organize following files from VS 2013 Premium or Ultimate (Demo is enough!) a. Interop.UIAutomationClient.dll b. UIAComWrapper.dll 2. Create a new unit test project (or edit the references) 3. Reference the DW.CodedUI 4. Reference UIAComWrapper.dll 5. Add Interop.UIAutomationClient.dll as existing file to the project with build action on "None" and "Copy Always". Or do a postbuild event, the file just need to lay beside the DW.CodedUI.dll in the output directory.
=> Now you can execute UI tests in usual [TestClass] objects.
